reviewText: His timing is great but his humor is offensive.  I don't care about "dirty words," I don't care about allusions to sex, but I do mind destructive prejudice pretending to be humor.  It's one thing to "make fun" of one's own ethnic/religious group...it's quite another to ascribe the most heinous characteristics, very often not even pretending that it's humor, to someone else's.
If you want a collection of Jackie Mason - a unique comedian who won't be around forever - this should be part of your collection.
I enjoyed jackie mason show. I recommend  it to the whole family.
